-c , --convert <filename | suffix | filename+suffix>
Runs edway non-interactively to convert files to another format.
The argument is normally the suffix indicating the format desired,
such as mp3 or ogg. However, if only one file is to be converted,
the argument may also be the desired name of the output file,
with or without a suffix. See help on writable file formats for a list of suffixes.
